  "prompt": "Is it forbidden in Islam to name your child Allah?",
  "response": "Yes, it is considered inappropriate and forbidden in Islam to name a child \"Allah.\" The name \"Allah\" is the unique and sacred name of God in Islam, and it is reserved solely for the divine being. Muslims are encouraged to show the utmost respect for the name and hence refrain from using \"Allah\" as a personal name for anyone other than the supreme deity. While names that reflect servitude to Allah, like Abdullah (meaning \"servant of Allah\"), are common and encouraged, directly naming a child \"Allah\" would be seen as disrespectful and inappropriate.",
